# Mission Specification Template

Use this template for every mission you design.

## Format
```
**B-[Rank initial]-[#]. [Short title]**

- Task. One paragraph with exact outcome.
- Evidence. Required links. Example: repo tag, explorer tx, NERN item, Dev Hub page, video.
- Acceptance. Binary checks reviewers follow.
```

## Mission Code Structure
- B = Builder track
- Rank initial: I (Initiate), A (Ascendant), V (Vanguard), P (Prime), M (Mythic)
- # = Sequential number within rank

## Task Section
- One paragraph maximum.
- State the exact outcome.
- Use active voice and second person.

## Evidence Section
- List all required links.
- Specify format: repo URL, tag/commit, explorer link, NERN link, video, etc.
- Be explicit about what must be included.

## Acceptance Section
- Binary checks only.
- Reviewers must be able to verify in under 15 minutes.
- No subjective criteria.